✅ What Is EBS CSI Driver?

The Amazon EBS CSI Driver allows Kubernetes in Amazon Web Services EKS to dynamically create EBS volumes when you create a PVC.

It runs as an EKS Add-on named:

aws-ebs-csi-driver
✅ Production Architecture (Best Practice)

You need:

EKS Cluster

OIDC provider enabled

IAM Role for Service Account (IRSA)

EKS Add-on referencing that IAM role

✅ Step 1: Enable OIDC Provider
data "tls_certificate" "oidc" {
  url = aws_eks_cluster.hdr.identity[0].oidc[0].issuer
}

resource "aws_iam_openid_connect_provider" "eks" {
  url             = aws_eks_cluster.hdr.identity[0].oidc[0].issuer
  client_id_list  = ["sts.amazonaws.com"]
  thumbprint_list = [data.tls_certificate.oidc.certificates[0].sha1_fingerprint]
}
✅ Step 2: Create IAM Role for EBS CSI (IRSA)
data "aws_iam_policy_document" "ebs_csi_assume_role_policy" {
  statement {
    actions = ["sts:AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity"]

    principals {
      type        = "Federated"
      identifiers = [aws_iam_openid_connect_provider.eks.arn]
    }

    condition {
      test     = "StringEquals"
      variable = "${replace(aws_eks_cluster.hdr.identity[0].oidc[0].issuer, "https://", "")}:sub"
      values   = ["system:serviceaccount:kube-system:ebs-csi-controller-sa"]
    }
  }
}

resource "aws_iam_role" "ebs_csi_driver_role" {
  name               = "hdr-ebs-csi-driver-role"
  assume_role_policy = data.aws_iam_policy_document.ebs_csi_assume_role_policy.json
}
✅ Step 3: Attach Required Policy
resource "aws_iam_role_policy_attachment" "ebs_csi_policy" {
  role       = aws_iam_role.ebs_csi_driver_role.name
  policy_arn = "arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/service-role/AmazonEBSCSIDriverPolicy"
}
✅ Step 4: Create EKS Add-on
resource "aws_eks_addon" "ebs_csi_driver" {
  cluster_name             = aws_eks_cluster.hdr.name
  addon_name               = "aws-ebs-csi-driver"
  service_account_role_arn = aws_iam_role.ebs_csi_driver_role.arn

  resolve_conflicts_on_update = "PRESERVE"

  depends_on = [
    aws_eks_node_group.hdr
  ]
}
✅ Step 5: Apply
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
✅ Step 6: Verify
aws eks update-kubeconfig --name hdr-cluster --region ap-south-1
kubectl get pods -n kube-system | grep ebs

You should see:

ebs-csi-controller
ebs-csi-node

Running ✅
